tool_description: Get Fighter Plane Data from Wikipedia, built to test rapid API
name: Get Plane Data from Wikipedia
title: Get Plane Data from Wikipedia

api_list.name: Get a single plane by name
api_list.description: This will break with some planes, as I haven't address the url encoding for the names
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://get-plane-data-from-wikipedia.p.rapidapi.com/plane/YF-23"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "get-plane-data-from-wikipedia.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
